    "or_image_text_UNPkBm": {
      "type": "or-image-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_YmnPUe": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Care + Cleaning Gold Vermeil Jewellery //"
          }
        },
        "richtext_QmitW8": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>All Phoria jewellery comes with a care card and polishing cloth with details of how to care for your piece. Gold vermeil requires some special care to ensure the gold plating remains intact.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_BpRaAW": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>We advise you to avoid contact with chemicals, so please remove your jewellery when using cleaning products, applying lotions like fake tan, cosmetics, perfumes or hairsprays, as these can damage the gold plating.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_yWjHAR": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>We also advise you to remove your jewellery before showering to reduce how exposed to moisture they are. Wait until any products are dry on your skin before putting your jewellery back on.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_TDmcrH": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>To clean your jewellery or to restore its shine, use the polishing cloth provided to you to gently wipe any fingerprints, dirt and oils. You can also use any commercial gold polishing cloth specifically designed for gold vermeil. Follow the product’s instructions and rub the cloth onto the jewellery in gentle, circular motions. Be careful not to over-polish, as excessive polishing can wear away the gold plating. Avoid abrasive materials like paper towels, as they can scratch the gold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_zYPWaJ": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>If your jewellery needs a more thorough cleaning, create a mixture of mild dish soap and warm water. Dip a soft cloth or a soft-bristle toothbrush in the soapy water, and gently scrub the silver. Rinse thoroughly with clean water and make sure to pat dry with a clean cloth.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_wQz3WH": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Avoid using ‘dip’ polish or abrasive jewellery cleaners on your gold vermeil jewellery as these contain harsh chemicals and can destroy your jewellery over time. We don’t recommend the use of any jewellery polishing cloths which have been treated with cleaners or polishing agents.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_tKde3U": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Be aware that gold plating on vermeil jewellery may wear over time, especially on areas that receive a lot of friction or contact, it can also depend on factors like how well it’s cared for and how often it’s worn. If the gold begins to show signs of wear or tarnish please feel free to get in touch at hello@phoriajewellery.com to find out more about our reconditioning service.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
